<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1905-03-28T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1905-03-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="639" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d639">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to Ambassador <persName type="to">Clayton</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1905-03-28"><hi rend="italic">March 28,
                                1905</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 1262.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your
                            dispatch, No. 2708, of the 16th instant, acknowledging the Department’s
                            telegram of the 14th instant. * * *</p>
                        <p>Your representations to the Mexican Government regarding the
                            effectiveness of Mexican precautions against the Yaquis and your course
                            in the matter are approved by the Department. You will press for due
                            protection for American citizens in Sonora.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Alvey A. Adee.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>